Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Peel and chop the @onion{1} into 2cm pieces
and peel and finely chop the @garlic cloves{2}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{1}
and set aside.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and fry your onion and
garlic gently for about ~{5%minutes} until softened. Add the @British beef mince{500},
turn the heat up slightly and cook for ~{10%minutes}, stirring occasionally until
the mince is browned all over.

Boil the @water{100}(ml), as stated in the ingredient list, and dissolve the
@beef stock pot{1} in it. Add half the @chopped tomatoes{1%12oz can}, all your stock
and @tomato purée{1} to your mince in the frying pan and stir well. Add the
@smoked paprika{3/4%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and simmer for
~{5%minutes} on medium-low heat, until thickened. Take off the heat and allow to
cool for ~{5%minutes} before assembling the rolypolys!

> Get your sombreros out, wrap yourself in a stripy blanket and get ready for a
> Mexican-style meal. Flour tortillas stuffed with tasty mince and smothered in
> a cheesy sauce … making your mouth water? Get the kids to help with prep,
> whether it's grating cheese or rolling up tortillas, they will be sure to
> enjoy their roly polys if they've had a hand in making them. Don't forget
> the cold beers and a slice of lime!

Divide your mince mixture between the @flour tortillas{8} and spread over each
tortilla. Roll up to enclose the meat and pack all your rolls tightly in an
#ovenproof dish{}.

Put a #pot{} of water on to boil for your beans. Spoon the remaining chopped
tomatoes over your rolls.

Put the @crème fraîche{1} in a #bowl{} and add in three-quarters of your cheese.
Stir together, then spoon your cheesy mixture over your tortillas, scatter your
remaining cheese on top. Pop in your #oven{} on a high shelf for
~{10-15%minutes}, until golden-brown.

Cut the tops and bottoms off the @green beans{3}. Tip: This is called top and
tailing! Cut them in half and add to the boiling water. Simmer for
~{3-5%minutes}, until just tender. Drain and serve with your beef roly polys
and enjoy!